title: New: Lana Del Rey – Blue Jeans (Live at the Premises)
body:
Thanks partly to [Hipster Runoff](http://www.hipsterrunoff.com/2011/09/lana-del-rey-next-overrated-marginally-talented-totally-hot-female-indie.html), the blogosphere has turned on [Miss **Del Rey**.](http://admin.crackintheroad.com/music/9518-new-video-lana-del-rey-video-games/ "New & Video: Lana Del Rey – Video Games") In many ways the attitude is immature and fickle, but of course when it comes to runoff, that’s the very point. The rest of the blogging community however, doesn’t quite have the postmodern swagger to offer such regurgitated venom.

Regardless of the debate this new found information on Del Rey provoked, the artist was undoubtedly once loved my the community. So it’s nice that Del Rey is plodding along in spite of the now dwindling support from the writers that were so pivotal in her emergence. Below is an example of her ‘plodding along’, if you can even call it that; she might not be the most conceptually evolutionally artist we once thought she was, but the girl can still write a killer pop song.
